ere anybody can buy, trade, and make whatever NFTs they want.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It wasn\u2019t until OpenSea came along that any of these things were possible. Even though it\u2019s technically a marketplace for NFTs, OpenSea serves as a user interface layer between the <a rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https:\/\/crypto-academy.org\/what-is-blockchain\/\">blockchain<\/a> and the general public, making NFTs accessible to everyone.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">With OpenSea, you don\u2019t need any previous experience to make NFTs. To get started, you\u2019ll need a collection of NFTs. Afterward, you\u2019ll be able to upload NFTs in the required format.\u00a0<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">As a result of their fascination with the introduction of the NFT series CryptoKitties, software engineers Alex Atallah and Devin Finzer launched OpenSea in 2017. They saw the potential of NFTs to allow genuine ownership of digital objects for the first time.<\/span><\/p>\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">How OpenSea Works<\/span><\/h2>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">There is no centralized body in charge of transactions on OpenSea\u2019s marketplace since it is non-custodial. Self-executing smart contracts are used to ensure fair trading instead. On OpenSea, a transaction is either completed, and both parties participate, or it does not occur, making the platform very secure.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Since OpenSea is a peer-to-peer market, there isn\u2019t any middleman to get in the way of transactions. Despite this, the platform maintains a 2.5% share of each sale.\u00a0<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Using the Wyvern Protocol, which is a series of smart contracts on the <a rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https:\/\/crypto-academy.org\/what-is-ethereum-a-step-by-step-guide\/\">Ethereum<\/a> blockchain, OpenSea\u2019s structure is able to buy and sell unique digital goods. In addition to supporting Ethereum, <a rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https:\/\/crypto-academy.org\/polygon-matic-staking\/\">Polygon<\/a>, and <a rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https:\/\/crypto-academy.org\/klaytn-price-prediction\/\">Klatyn<\/a>, the platform is cross-blockchain compatible.<\/span><\/p>\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">OpenSea\u2019s Advantages<\/span><\/h2>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Opensea\u2019s Polygon-based <a rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https:\/\/crypto-academy.org\/gas-fees-meaning-what-are-gas-fees\/\">gas<\/a>-free marketplace allows artists to mint NFTs for free, which is a major advantage for them. Another feature of OpenSea is that the artist of an NFT may opt to receive a royalty fee for every secondary-market sale of the token indefinitely.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Buying NFTs on OpenSea is easy because you can search for them by price, status, native blockchain, and rarity. Buyers may also check the purchase history of each NFT, such as how many times it was sold, who acquired it, and its pricing.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Another advantage is OpenSea\u2019s active community; as previously stated, the biggest NFT market is OpenSea. According to reports, OpenSea has more than a million registered members and is actively engaged in the community.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">More than a dozen digital <a rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https:\/\/crypto-academy.org\/cryptocurrency-wallet-definition\/\">wallets<\/a> are supported by OpenSea, with <a rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https:\/\/crypto-academy.org\/metamask-review\/\">MetaMask<\/a> and <a rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https:\/\/crypto-academy.org\/coinbase-review\/\">Coinbase<\/a> Wallet being among the most popular.<\/span><\/p>\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">OpenSea\u2019s Drawbacks<\/span><\/h2>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">One of the primary drawbacks of OpenSea is that due to it utilizing the Ethereum blockchain, there can be significant gas fee prices during peak network congestion. To solve this issue, OpenSea provided cross-chain functionality for Polygon and built a gas-free marketplace. This problem is also being addressed by Ethereum 2.0, a much more eco-friendly and cost-efficient <a rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https:\/\/crypto-academy.org\/pos-meaning-in-crypto-what-is-proof-of-stake\/\">proof-of-stake<\/a> version of the system.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">OpenSea has also experienced a service provider outage, ongoing database difficulties, higher API failures, and slow response times. As a result of these problems, the company now publishes a monthly report on website reliability that details the problems that have occurred in the previous month and the efforts that are being made to fix them.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Misuse of OpenSea has resulted in financial losses for some customers. In September 2021, OpenSea\u2019s head of product was suspected of trading NFTs based on insider knowledge. The executive was utilizing hidden digital wallets to purchase NFT drops before they could be displayed on the platform\u2019s site and sell them soon after being released to the public.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In January 2022, people discovered a heist on OpenSea worth 332 ETH.\u00a0 OpenSea claimed it contacted harmed users individually and compensated them. But added that the issue is intrinsic to blockchain markets and told all users how to manage their accounts to prevent this vulnerability.<\/span><\/p>\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">How To Buy An NFT On OpenSea<\/span><\/h2>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Without wasting any more time, here is a little tutorial on how to purchase NFTs on OpenSea.<\/span><\/p>\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Step 1: Fund Your Digital Wallet<\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">To purchase NFTs, you\u2019ll need a digital wallet that has funds in it. You will purchase items on OpenSea using the cryptocurrency Ethereum (ETH). For this article, we\u2019ll utilize MetaMask, one of the most popular digital wallets for NFTs.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">If you don\u2019t already have a digital wallet, go over to metamask.io to download it as a browser extension and link it to OpenSea. Go to OpenSea and click on profile in the upper right bar to do this. You\u2019ll be led to a new page requesting you to link to your wallet and then choose\u00a0 MetaMask.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Allow OpenSea to use your digital wallet and sign the signature request by granting it the required rights.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Once it has been set up, you may begin browsing the OpenSea marketplace for NFTs. Go over to the MetaMask wallet and choose \u201cBuy\u201d to make a crypto deposit or use a debit\/credit card if you don\u2019t already have Ethereum in your MetaMask wallet.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"343\" class=\"size-full wp-image-25078 aligncenter\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=\" http:=\"\" alt=\"&quot;Connecting\" data-lazy- data-lazy- data-recalc-dims=\"1\" data-lazy-src=\"https:\/\/www.newsdgtl.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/image2-2.png\"\/><\/p>\n<p><noscript><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"343\" class=\"size-full wp-image-25078 aligncenter\" src=\"https:\/\/www.newsdgtl.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/image2-2.png\" alt=\"&quot;Connecting\"   data-recalc-dims=\"1\"\/><\/noscript><\/p>\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Step 2: Choose An NFT<\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Firstly, you will need to select the NFT you wish to buy. Log in to your OpenSea account and choose \u201cExplore\u201d from the menu. Then, you will see all of the NFT collections that are available to you.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You may narrow down your search on the top right bar by filtering it.\u00a0 You can choose filters such as Trending, Top, Art, Collectibles, Music, Photography, etc.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"366\" class=\"size-full wp-image-25079 aligncenter\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=\" http:=\"\" alt=\"&quot;Choosing\" data-lazy- data-lazy- data-recalc-dims=\"1\" data-lazy-src=\"https:\/\/www.newsdgtl.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/image4.png\"\/><\/p>\n<p><noscript><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"366\" class=\"size-full wp-image-25079 aligncenter\" src=\"https:\/\/www.newsdgtl.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/image4.png\" alt=\"&quot;Choosing\"   data-recalc-dims=\"1\"\/><\/noscript><\/p>\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Step 3: Buy The NFT Or Make An Offer<\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A purchase can be made immediately, or you can make an offer when you see an NFT you want. The \u201cPlace Bid\u201d feature exists on certain NFTs if you want to make an official offer to buy a specific NFT. When you see an NFT like this, check the number of previous bids to discover how much you can bid.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Every bid on OpenSea needs to be at least 5% greater than the one before it in order to be accepted. In this case, we\u2019ll only purchase at a predetermined price for demonstration purposes.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"354\" class=\"wp-image-25082 size-full aligncenter\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=\" http:=\"\" alt=\"&quot;Buying\" data-lazy- data-lazy- data-recalc-dims=\"1\" data-lazy-src=\"https:\/\/www.newsdgtl.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/image6-1.png\"\/><\/p>\n<p><noscript><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"354\" class=\"wp-image-25082 size-full aligncenter\" src=\"https:\/\/www.newsdgtl.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/image6-1.png\" alt=\"&quot;Buying\"   data-recalc-dims=\"1\"\/><\/noscript><\/p>\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Step 4: Finalise Your Purchase<\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">When you\u2019ve discovered the perfect NFT for you. Buy it by clicking \u201cBuy now.\u201d\u00a0<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">After doing so, you\u2019ll find information on the NFT, such as its name, collection, subtotal, and total. Go over to Confirm Checkout.\u00a0<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Then, OpenSea will load your MetaMask digital wallet onto your computer. A breakdown of your purchases, including estimated gas costs and processing times, can be found here.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Please bear in mind that cutting the gas fees will significantly impact transaction speed. If you want to use MetaMask to make a purchase, wait until the Ethereum network is less congested.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Press the confirm button when you\u2019re ready to make a purchase, and sit tight while your payment is being processed.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"357\" class=\"size-full wp-image-25083 aligncenter\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=\" http:=\"\" alt=\"&quot;Finalizing\" data-lazy- data-lazy- data-recalc-dims=\"1\" data-lazy-src=\"https:\/\/www.newsdgtl.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/image3.png\"\/><\/p>\n<p><noscript><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"357\" class=\"size-full wp-image-25083 aligncenter\" src=\"https:\/\/www.newsdgtl.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/image3.png\" alt=\"&quot;Finalizing\"   data-recalc-dims=\"1\"\/><\/noscript><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Your brand-new NFT will be added to your collection in a matter of seconds at most. Once you\u2019ve returned to your profile, wait patiently for your new NFT to show up.<\/span><\/p>\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">How To Sell An NFT On OpenSea<\/span><\/h2>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">If you want to sell an NFT on OpenSea, simply click on \u201cSell\u201d at the top right bar of your screen, and you\u2019ll be sent to a new page where you can fill in the terms of the sale.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Choosing if you want to sell it at a set price or a scheduled auction, the currency, and the expiry date are all of the options you need to consider before selling your NFT. OpenSea takes a 2.5 percent cut of every sale in addition to the standard listing fee.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Once you\u2019ve selected your NFT, go to the \u201cDetails\u201d section by clicking on it and scrolling all the way down. There, click on \u201cContract Address,\u201d and then you will be sent to the Etherscan page for your NFTs address.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Copy the address and then go back to your MetaMask wallet. The option \u201cImport Tokens\u201d is located below. Select \u201cCustom Token\u201d from the drop-down menu. Paste the specific address you copied from the Etherscan page.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"353\" class=\"size-full wp-image-25084 aligncenter\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=\" http:=\"\" alt=\"&quot;Selling\" data-lazy- data-lazy- data-recalc-dims=\"1\" data-lazy-src=\"https:\/\/www.newsdgtl.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/image5.png\"\/><\/p>\n<p><noscript><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"353\" class=\"size-full wp-image-25084 aligncenter\" src=\"https:\/\/www.newsdgtl.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/image5.png\" alt=\"&quot;Selling\"   data-recalc-dims=\"1\"\/><\/noscript><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A token symbol is simply the public nametag, and Token Decimals are merely a means of seeing your NFTs.\u00a0 It won\u2019t affect the amount you are holding.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">We will add \u201c0\u201d in this scenario, and then we\u2019ll go ahead and click on add custom token.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You\u2019ve successfully listed an NFT for sale on OpenSea. Congratulations!<\/span><\/p>\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">How To Create An NFT On OpenSea<\/span><\/h2>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">OpenSea users can not only buy and sell NFTs, but they can easily mint their own NFTs using an easy-to-use method provided by the platform. Here is a small tutorial on how to do just that.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Go to \u201cCreate\u201d or \u201cCollection\u201d if you\u2019re minting a collection to begin the process of creating your NFT.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Then, enter the name of your NFT or Collection.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"359\" class=\"size-full wp-image-25085 aligncenter\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=\" http:=\"\" alt=\"&quot;Creating\" data-lazy- data-lazy- data-recalc-dims=\"1\" data-lazy-src=\"https:\/\/www.newsdgtl.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/image1-4.png\"\/><\/p>\n<p><noscript><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"359\" class=\"size-full wp-image-25085 aligncenter\" src=\"https:\/\/www.newsdgtl.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/image1-4.png\" alt=\"&quot;Creating\"   data-recalc-dims=\"1\"\/><\/noscript><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Keep in mind that your OpenSea URL can be customized, and you can also add a description of up to 1000 characters.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">To make it easier for others to locate your NFT on OpenSea, you can categorize it and add any social and website links.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">If you\u2019d like to include a royalty percentage, keep in mind that it can only be as high as 10%.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Once you\u2019ve chosen your blockchain (Ethereum or Polygon), click Create to complete the process.<\/span><\/p>\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">OpenSea Features<\/span><\/h2>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">OpenSea, one of the world\u2019s most well-known NFT marketplaces, has several special features that set it apart from the crowd. Here are a few of them.<\/span><\/p>\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Multi Crypto Wallet Options<\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Many NFT marketplaces are dependent on just a few wallets. OpenSea, on the other hand, supports plenty of them. The following are a few of the digital wallets that are compatible with the platform: Coinbase, Portis, MetaMask, <a rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https:\/\/crypto-academy.org\/trust-wallet-review\/\">TrustWallet<\/a>, Bitski, Dapper, Kaikas, and many more.<\/span><\/p>\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Completely Free<\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In the beginning, you can use OpenSea for free. However, each sale on the marketplace is charged a 2.5 percent fee by the site. On the other hand, there aren\u2019t any monthly or recurring charges.<\/span><\/p>\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Gifting<\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">OpenSea\u2019s gifting function is its unique selling point. To gift an NFT, all you have to do is send someone the Ethereum address of a wallet. The developer will then provide the asset to a trader, who will subsequently add it to their current collection of NFTs.<\/span><\/p>\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">NFT Minting<\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">As we mentioned above, users have the option of minting their own NFTs in addition to purchasing and selling pre-existing ones. You\u2019ll have to gain access to the OpenSea API to accomplish this. You may do this after you\u2019ve created an account on the platform. Creating a new type of NFT that isn\u2019t supported by the platform is a straightforward process.<\/span><\/p>\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Mobile Application<\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">OpenSea is a very up-to-date platform. Because of their effort to create an NFT marketplace that is accessible and simple for all dealers and collectors, they are unmatched.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Their smartphone app, for instance, is a good example. The program has a clean interface, is simple to use, and is absolutely free. OpenSea allows you to monitor your NFTs from anywhere with an internet connection, making it easy to keep records of your transactions.<\/span><\/p>\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Tips On Using OpenSea<\/span><\/h2>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Ethereum gas costs are expected to fall short. As of now, though, gas prices are quite high. As long as you don\u2019t feel the need to rush, you may wait until gas costs are cheaper before starting the collection. Late in the evening and early in the morning are often the best times to get a deal. You should never pay more than necessary.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Keep your NFTs until you\u2019ve finished listing a collection before you sell them. The first step is to set up a collection for your NFTs. To complete the collection, you add the NFTs one by one. Your whole collection of NFTs is transferred to the Ethereum blockchain as soon as you sell one on OpenSea. After that, adding additional NFTs costs more Ethereum.\u00a0<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Don\u2019t hope to sell a lot of NFTs in the first few months. NFTs by new artists are rarely purchased. NFT enthusiasts, on the other hand, are unlikely to leap right into OpenSea. As a collector of NFTs, you will have to market your collection to other collectors. It\u2019s important to show NFT collectors that you have a unique perspective and that you\u2019ll be around for the long term.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">OpenSea\u2019s transaction speed is critical for purchasing or minting NFTs, so make sure you select it correctly. In order to maximize your chances of successfully purchasing or minting an NFT, we recommend using a medium or high speed for NFTs. You run the risk of losing your gas fee if you select the low option, and the transaction is prone to failure.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Everything should be double-checked before the metadata is frozen.\u00a0\u00a0<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Once they purchase your NFT, serious customers want to know that the listing will not alter. It is, however, impossible to tamper with the information after it has been frozen. The item can be removed and re-minted if you can\u2019t sell it. However, this imposes significant gas expenses.<\/span><\/p>\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Staying Safe On OpenSea<\/span><\/h2>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Trading NFTs on OpenSea is not as difficult as you might imagine. Although there are many fraudsters in this industry, you should be aware that the market may be quite unpredictable at times.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It is fairly rare for individuals to lose their assets to fraudsters that use phishing or rug pulling to scam. Additionally, the NFT industry is plagued by wash traders, who inflate the trading volume of specific collections in order to make them more enticing to investors.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">However, it\u2019s crucial to remember that this is a relatively new sector that is mostly unregulated in the majority of jurisdictions, so caution should be used. As a result, it is vital to treat it as such and to take the required measures to protect your financial assets. Accepting bids should always be made with caution, and you should make sure the offer is already in your currency of choice before accepting it.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">If OpenSea customer service contacts you about a problem you\u2019re having, be extremely wary. This is a frequent ruse scammers use to gain access to your account. Even if someone appears to be from OpenSea support, never reveal your wallet\u2019s secret phrase or grant anybody else access to your device.<\/span><\/p>\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Other NFT Marketplaces Like OpenSea<\/span><\/h2>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">However, OpenSea is not the only NFT marketplace. Additionally, it claims the widest selection of categories and the lowest costs. However, other options are growing in popularity.<\/span><\/p>\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Rarible<\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Another well-known NFT marketplace is Rarible. Rarible\u2019s native token, RARI, is required for NFT purchases and sales inside the platform. This is distinct since RARI is a governance token. As a result, those who own RARI have a say in how the platform is run.<\/span><\/p>\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Fractional<\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Fractional, for example, provides a novel technique for minting and trading NFTs. By purchasing fractional ownership in major NFTs, consumers may save money and lower the entry barriers while still getting a portion of their preferred digital assets, as the name implies.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Other notable NFT markets include SuperRare, Foundation, Nifty Gateway, and Larva Labs, all of which have their own distinct characteristics.<\/span><\/p>\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)<\/span><\/h2>\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">What Currencies Can I Use On OpenSea?<\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">When it comes to OpenSea, the most prominent currencies are Ethereum (ETH), WETH (WETH), and DAI (DAI). Fiat currencies like USD and Euro are not yet supported, despite having over 150 different payment coins.<\/span><\/p>\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">What Wallets Does OpenSea Support?<\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Despite the fact that just a small number of crypto wallets are directly supported by OpenSea, this already covers the majority of those in use today. Some are designed for mobile devices, while others can be used on a variety of platforms. Your preferences will play a major role in deciding which one to choose. MetaMask, CoinBase, TrustWallet, Portis, Venly are some of the digital wallets that OpenSea supports.<\/span><\/p>\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Is OpenSea Safe?<\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">As a rule of thumb, yes. Measures have been put in place by OpenSea to keep an eye out for potentially harmful content and phishing schemes. To avoid being conned, you should conduct your own research on the NFT developers and stick to certified collections when purchasing NFTs from large public figures. Also, make sure you\u2019re on OpenSea.io at all times, and never reveal your wallet\u2019s recovery phrase to anyone.<\/span><\/p>\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">How Does OpenSea Make Money?<\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">All transactions that occur on the platform are subject to a minor fee charged by OpenSea. This tiny fee assists in the fulfillment of asset transfers and smart contract transactions in the shortest amount of time.<\/span><\/p>\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Takeaways<\/span><\/h2>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">OpenSea is one of the best marketplaces to buy, sell and create NFTs in an easy and simple way.<\/span><\/i><\/li>\n<li st